# lbkmk core

**lbkmk** reconciles multi-channel sales (Squarespace, Stripe, Square, TicketTailor), inventory, and itemized Xero invoicing so per-item revenue and stock are answerable beyond lump-sum bank feeds.

**Current phase:** documentation and proposal (no Phoenix app in repo until `mix.exs` exists). Confirm against the tree before assuming otherwise.

## Anchor documents

- `docs/domain-model.md` — vocabulary, entities, business rules (source of truth for terms)
- `docs/solution-proposal.md` — proposed solution shape

## Open questions (blocking)

Before design or implementation on any module, read `docs/domain-model.md` **§7 (vocabulary)** and **§8 (scope)**.

- Do not start work blocked by an unresolved question unless the owner explicitly accepts the risk.
- When planning, surface any open question that touches the feature area.
- Tag questions with `blocks: <feature>` when known (see `CLAUDE.md`).

## Stack notes

- **Phoenix LiveView** — planned application stack.
- **Ash Framework** — not in use; persistence is **Ecto** + `Repo` when code exists.

For commands, document naming, handoffs, worktrees, and external-agent workflow, see **`CLAUDE.md`** — this rule does not duplicate that file.
